m2Eclipse is an Eclipse extension that provides Maven integration for Eclipse. http://eclipse.org/m2e/
Subversive is an Eclipse extension that provides SVN integration for Eclipse. http://www.eclipse.org/subversive/

Eclipse is an open source community providing a leading development platform for Java and other languages built on an extensible framework. The Eclipse web site at http://www.eclipse.org/ gives access to the Eclipse tools and the wide range of official Eclipse projects that extend the basic platform.

The Eclipse framework can be extended by new components that provide additional functionality. Eclipse plug-ins are extensions to the Eclipse platform that implement one or more extension points defined by the platform or other plug-ins. Most of the functionality Eclipse framework itself is built as plug-ins. Plug-ins are usually grouped and packaged into features, which are the deployable units selectable from Eclipse update site. Plug-ins and features are here both referred to as Eclipse extensions.

Sonar is an open source tool for quality management that allow you to run a set of tests on your software. The Sonar Eclipse extension gives an Eclipse perspective in which the information is provided. http://www.sonarsource.org/
The Pax Runner Eclipse extension simplifies launching of OSGi based systems from within the Eclipse environment. Pax Runner is available from: http://team.ops4j.org/
Papyrus is an open source UML modelling tool based on the Eclipse UML2 framework and the Eclipse Modeling Framework (EMF). http://www.eclipse.org/modeling/mdt/papyrus/

MOFscript is a model-to-text transformation tool based on a meta-model independent language. The MOFscript tool is provided as an Eclipse plugin, with built-in support for using EMF and Eclipse UML2 models as input. http://www.eclipse.org/gmt/mofscript/
